# Kill port 3000

When the user says "kill 3000", run a PowerShell command to find the first PID
listening on port 3000 and terminate it.

Use this command:

```
$portPid = (netstat -ano | findstr ":3000" | Select-Object -First 1).ToString().Split()[-1]; if ($portPid) { taskkill /PID $portPid /F }
```